2026 Season Performance: As of April 2026, Antonelli leads the Formula 1 World Championship with 72 points after winning the Japanese Grand Prix.
Historic Milestones: Following his victory in China in 2026, he became the youngest-ever race winner at 19 years and, subsequently, the youngest-ever championship leader.
Mercedes Tenure: He replaced Lewis Hamilton at Mercedes in 2026, joining fellow Mercedes driver George Russell to form an all-British/Italian lineup.
Junior Career: Antonelli joined the Mercedes Junior Programme in 2019. His junior career was marked by significant success, including securing both German and Italian F4 titles, 
and winning the FIA Karting European Championship.
Driving Style: Antonelli is noted for his maturity in driving and ability to manage tire degradation, 
earning praise from team boss Toto Wolff for his "mature" racing performances.
